			type: "title",
			script: "In Module 01 we saw the five components of an agent: planning, tools, memory, safety, and human-in-the-loop. But here's the question that decides your design: who does what? Not every agent needs the same architecture. Some problems are solved by a single agent with a clear loop. Others need multiple agents coordinating. And the roles you assign—planner, executor, router, orchestrator—determine how reliable and scalable your system becomes. Let's go deeper into the architecture choices that pass production reviews.",
			title: "Agent Architecture Deep Dive",
