			script: "Let's frame the problem. Agents make multiple model calls per user interaction. A single request might trigger five, ten, or twenty inference calls as the agent plans, retrieves, acts, and reflects. Each call has latency. Each call has cost. At scale, small improvements compound. A ten percent latency reduction across ten calls saves a second per request. A ten percent cost reduction across millions of requests saves real money. GPU inference behaves differently from CPU. GPUs are built for parallel computation. They excel at batch processing: run many requests together, and throughput goes up. But batching adds latency—you wait for the batch to fill. So there's a tradeoff: low latency with small batches, high throughput with large batches. The right choice depends on your workload.",
