			type: "content-single",
			script: "Let's define what we mean by evaluation. An evaluation harness is a system that runs your agent against test cases and measures quality. Correctness: did the agent produce the right answer? Structure: does the output match the expected format—valid JSON, required fields? Grounding: is the response supported by retrieved context or tool results, or did the agent hallucinate? Regression: did a change make things worse? Run the same test set before and after. If scores drop, you've introduced a regression. Automated evaluators can check these dimensions. For correctness, you might use a model-as-judge: a separate model scores the output. For structure, use a parser: valid JSON or schema validation. For grounding, check that citations reference actual retrieved chunks or tool outputs. For hallucination, verify that factual claims appear in the context. These checks can run in CI: every pull request triggers the harness. Fail the build if regression is detected.",
